    ğŸ”¹ `--list`  --> ğŸ“œ List the ELF files that would be modified, but do not actually modify them.
    ğŸ”¹ `--only-compress` --> ğŸ“¦ Only check and strip compressed files.
    ğŸ”¹ `--fail-if-changed` --> ğŸš¨ Fail the build if any files were changed.
    ğŸ”¹ `--exclude *file*` --> ğŸš« Exclude this file or files from stripping. Wildcards can be used.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ dh_strip_nondeterminism
    ğŸ”¹ Strip non-deterministic information from all ELF files in the build directory.

    $ dh_strip_nondeterminism --list
    ğŸ”¹ List the ELF files that would be modified.

    $ dh_strip_nondeterminism --exclude usr/bin/foo --exclude usr/bin/bar
    ğŸ”¹ Strip non-deterministic information from all files except usr/bin/foo and usr/bin/bar.

